7.5.25  10:47 am   Hey Bill, on some days I wake up and have this weird sense of confusion. Like I can have plenty of really good days in a row where everything works fine, I have energy, my routine is working, my project is going well and I'm just overall confident. And then sometimes the next day, completely out of nowhere my brain is like doubting everything and giving me all sorts of reasons why things aren't gonna work out and I'm just... confused? Have you dealt with this before and do you maybe have a solution to this?

      this will always happen from time to time, and there's no way around it, but here's why you should be glad: without this part of the cycle, the other parts wouldn't be any good. they literally would not be defined as anything good, in comparison to anything. no matter what ocean wave you have, there is a downside to the wave. the only way to avoid the downside is to avoid the entire wave altogether, thus also avoiding the upside

7.4.25  2:11 pm   The way I like to think of genres is that, instead of being strict categories that artists or songs have to fit in, they're just labels you can put on a song that describe a specific aspect of the song, be it when it was made, the instrumentation used, the way it's produced, the lyrical content, etc. and since most songs are quite multifaceted, most songs can have several genres attributed to them, and this combination of genres, together, constitutes an (albeit rough and imperfect) description of the song, that gives you a (rough and imperfect) idea of what to expect from that song. What do you think?

      that's great as long as you can make up as many different names and terms as you need to
